{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot"]]},"seeAlsoSections":[{"generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Differences","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Variants","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Exports","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Signals","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/CustomTypes","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/BindingNodes"],"anchor":"Articles-and-Tutorials","title":"Articles and Tutorials"}],"metadata":{"role":"article","title":"Running Code in the Godot Editor","modules":[{"name":"SwiftGodot"}],"roleHeading":"Article"},"sections":[],"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"level":2,"text":"Overview","type":"heading","anchor":"overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"To achieve this, you can include the ","type":"text"},{"code":".tool","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" parameter to the "},{"code":"@Godot","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" macro,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"like this:"}]},{"code":["@Godot(.tool)","class Line3D: MeshInstance3D {","","    \/\/ This will be called in the editor","    override func _ready() {","\t\/\/ Run some code here","    }","","    \/\/ And so will this one","    override func _process(delta _: Double) {","\t\/\/ Check if we are running in the editor, or in the game","        if Engine.isEditorHint() {","            doEditorWork ()","        } else {","\t    doGameWork ()","\t}","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can use it for doing many things, but it is mostly useful in level design"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"for visually presenting things that are hard to predict ourselves. Here are some","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"use cases:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"parag